---------------------------------
|   Pseudocode for calculator   |
---------------------------------
Stage: start. Accept input number. if first number is not filled remove current display and display input, if 
first number is filled add input to the current display. After choosing a number the user can either choose a 
operator or press sum. if sum is pressed do nothing, if operator is pressed store input nr in nr1, store operator 
input in operator variable, set firstNrFilled to false and set stage to nr1Operator 

Stage: nr1Operator. At this stage we have nr1 and operator. From here, the user can input a new number, press operator or 
press sum. 

If sum is pressed, store display value to nr2, run and store sum function with nr1, nr2 and operator to sum 
variable. Set stage to sum and firstNrFilled to false. Pressing sum again should do nothing. 

If operator is pressed, store display value to nr2, run and store sum function. Display sum value, update operator 
with the new operator, set firstNrFilled to false and set stage to nr1nr2Operator. 


stage: sum. Here we have nr1, nr2 and operator. The user can press a new operator or enter a new value then press 
new operator. If the user presses new operator, store current display to nr1. 